qbDwsMIB.name: qbDwsMIB
qbDwsMIB.description: This module defines additional objects for the provisioning and management of DWS links in Quantum bridge devices.

QbPvcConnKind.name: QbPvcConnKind
QbPvcConnKind.description: A connection type that can be provisioned.

QbDwsIfStatus.name: QbDwsIfStatus
QbDwsIfStatus.description: The status of the DWS Interface

QbDwsSrvStatus.name: QbDwsSrvStatus
QbDwsSrvStatus.description: The service status of the DWS Interface

QbAtmAal5EncapsType.name: QbAtmAal5EncapsType
QbAtmAal5EncapsType.description: The type of data encapsulation used over the AAL5 layer.

qbDwsSysRangeMode.name: qbDwsSysRangeMode
qbDwsSysRangeMode.description: The object that indicates a system wide range mode. When read, this object always returns the value 'ready(1)'. Setting this object to rangeAll(2) causes ranging of all IOTs that connect to this OAS.

qbSysIotRecoverMode.name: qbSysIotRecoverMode
qbSysIotRecoverMode.description: The object allows to set the IOT auto-recovery feature on the IOAS. Auto-recovery is global in scope, so when it is enabled, auto-recovery is attempted for all IOTs that are attached to the IOAS.

qbDwsNetTable.name: qbDwsNetTable
qbDwsNetTable.description: The Quantum Bridge PON Interface Table contains extensions of the standard MIB Interface Table, one entry per IOAS DWS interface. The table contains read-only objects and shows MIB objects for every Network interface

qbDwsNetEntry.name: qbDwsNetEntry
qbDwsNetEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum Bridge DWS Interface Table that contains the Network interface's specific objects.

qbDwsNetIfIndex.name: qbDwsNetIfIndex
qbDwsNetIfIndex.description: The value of this object is the same as the corresponding ifIndex of the Network Interface in the ifTable.

qbDwsNetBw.name: qbDwsNetBw
qbDwsNetBw.description: The object indicates the total bandwidth rate that is available for reservation on this interface. This object is specified in Bits per second.

qbDwsNetAllocatedBw.name: qbDwsNetAllocatedBw
qbDwsNetAllocatedBw.description: The object indicates the total bandwidth rate that is currently subscribed. The subscribed bandwidth rate consists of the bandwidth rate allocated for all provisoned connections. This object is specified in Bits per sec(Bps).

qbDwsNetAvailableBw.name: qbDwsNetAvailableBw
qbDwsNetAvailableBw.description: The portion of this interface's capacity in bits per sec that is available for data traffic. This variable is adjusted for the allocated bandwidth. The formula for calculating this value is qbDwsNetBw - qbDwsNetAllocatedBw This object is specified in Bps.

qbDwsNetAllocatedUbrBw.name: qbDwsNetAllocatedUbrBw
qbDwsNetAllocatedUbrBw.description: The object indicates the total number of bandwidth that are currently allocated for packet/ubr traffic. This object is specified in Bps.

qbDwsNetAllocatedCbrBw.name: qbDwsNetAllocatedCbrBw
qbDwsNetAllocatedCbrBw.description: The object indicates the total number of bandwidth that is currently allocated for CBR traffic. This object is specified in Bps.

qbDwsNetNumCbrConn.name: qbDwsNetNumCbrConn
qbDwsNetNumCbrConn.description: The object indicates the total number of inactive and in-service CBR connections that are currently provisioned on this interface.

qbDwsNetNumUbrConn.name: qbDwsNetNumUbrConn
qbDwsNetNumUbrConn.description: The object indicates the total number of inactive and in-serice UBR connections that are currently provisioned on this interface.

qbDwsNetNumIot.name: qbDwsNetNumIot
qbDwsNetNumIot.description: The number of IOTs that are provisioned on the Network interface.

qbDwsNetTxStatus.name: qbDwsNetTxStatus
qbDwsNetTxStatus.description: This objects indicates the status of the DWS transmitter. The trap is generated by the SNMP agent when the IOAS DWS transmitter problem is detected. The trap contains the DWS module interface index.

qbDwsNetTxStatusLastChange.name: qbDwsNetTxStatusLastChange
qbDwsNetTxStatusLastChange.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the time this DWS Interface entered its current status state.

qbDwsNetLosIotAddr.name: qbDwsNetLosIotAddr
qbDwsNetLosIotAddr.description: The object contains the address of the IOT for which a Los condition is detected. This indicates that no signal was detected within the expected time slot window. Note: The Los indication at the IOAS DWS card is a signal that an IOT is non-functioning.

qbDwsNetLosIotTime.name: qbDwsNetLosIotTime
qbDwsNetLosIotTime.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the time when the qbDwsNetIotLos condition was detected.

qbDwsNetEncryptStatus.name: qbDwsNetEncryptStatus
qbDwsNetEncryptStatus.description: The object that enables and disables encryption on this interface.

qbDwsNetRangeMode.name: qbDwsNetRangeMode
qbDwsNetRangeMode.description: The object that indicates a range mode. When read, this object always returns the value 'ready(1)'. Setting this object to rangeAll(2) causes ranging of all IOTs connected to this interface.

qbDwsNetRxTsCount.name: qbDwsNetRxTsCount
qbDwsNetRxTsCount.description: The total number of successfully received time slots.

qbDwsNetTxTsCount.name: qbDwsNetTxTsCount
qbDwsNetTxTsCount.description: The total number of successfully transmitted time slots.

qbDwsNetRxMissingTs.name: qbDwsNetRxMissingTs
qbDwsNetRxMissingTs.description: The number received time slots that have been missed.

qbDwsNetRxIllegalTs.name: qbDwsNetRxIllegalTs
qbDwsNetRxIllegalTs.description: The number illegal received time slots that have been detected.

qbDwsNetTxJabberTs.name: qbDwsNetTxJabberTs
qbDwsNetTxJabberTs.description: The number jabber transmitted time slots that have been detected.

qbDwsNetTxOutOfFrameTs.name: qbDwsNetTxOutOfFrameTs
qbDwsNetTxOutOfFrameTs.description: The number out of frame transmitted timeslots that have been detected.

qbDwsNetTxHdrCrcTsErrs.name: qbDwsNetTxHdrCrcTsErrs
qbDwsNetTxHdrCrcTsErrs.description: The number transmitted timeslots with the header protection error that have been detected.

qbDwsNetOamRequests.name: qbDwsNetOamRequests
qbDwsNetOamRequests.description: The number of OAM requests. These OAM requests are originated by the IOAS and sent to downstream IOTs.

qbDwsNetOamResponses.name: qbDwsNetOamResponses
qbDwsNetOamResponses.description: The number of OAM responses. These responses are generated by IOTs in response to downstream requests.

qbDwsNetOamEvents.name: qbDwsNetOamEvents
qbDwsNetOamEvents.description: The number of OAM events. These events are originated by IOT devices to signal abnormal conditions.

qbDwsNetOamBadMsgs.name: qbDwsNetOamBadMsgs
qbDwsNetOamBadMsgs.description: The total number of bad OAM messages.

qbDwsNetLoopBack.name: qbDwsNetLoopBack
qbDwsNetLoopBack.description: The Loopback status of this DWS port. Writing configures the port to go into the loopback mode. When placed in loopback mode the DWS port does a 'payload' loopback.

qbDwsIotIfConfTable.name: qbDwsIotIfConfTable
qbDwsIotIfConfTable.description: The Quantum DWS interface table. One entry per each IOT's DWS interface.

qbDwsIotIfConfEntry.name: qbDwsIotIfConfEntry
qbDwsIotIfConfEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum Bridge DWS Interface Table. The ifIndex is a DWS interface index from ifTable.

qbDwsIotIfIndex.name: qbDwsIotIfIndex
qbDwsIotIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this interface in the ifTable.

qbDwsIotNetIfIndex.name: qbDwsIotNetIfIndex
qbDwsIotNetIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of this PON interface in the ifTable.

qbDwsIotIfConfEqDelay.name: qbDwsIotIfConfEqDelay
qbDwsIotIfConfEqDelay.description: The equal Delay time (in hundredths of a second).

qbDwsIotIfConfWaveLength.name: qbDwsIotIfConfWaveLength
qbDwsIotIfConfWaveLength.description: The wave length value for this DWS interface.

qbDwsIotIfUbrBw.name: qbDwsIotIfUbrBw
qbDwsIotIfUbrBw.description: The object indicates the total UBR bandwidth rate that is reserved for a given IOT interface. This object is specified in Bits per second.

qbDwsIotIfCbrBw.name: qbDwsIotIfCbrBw
qbDwsIotIfCbrBw.description: The object indicates the total CBR bandwidth rate that is reserved for a given IOT interface. This object is specified in Bits per second.

qbDwsIotIfTxStatus.name: qbDwsIotIfTxStatus
qbDwsIotIfTxStatus.description: This objects indicates the status of the IOT DWS Port. The txFailure(2) state indicates that the laser transmitter failed. The rxFailure(3) state indicates that no signal was detected within the expected timeslot window. It signals that there is a problem with the DWS port receiver. When this object is changed, the ifOperStatus and ifLastChnaged of this interface must also be changed. Note: The trap is generated by the SNMP agent when the IOT DWS status is changed. The trap contains the IOAS DWS card interface index and IOT address.

qbDwsIotIfTxStatusLastChange.name: qbDwsIotIfTxStatusLastChange
qbDwsIotIfTxStatusLastChange.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the time this DWS Interface enters its current status state.

qbDwsIotIfLastRangeTime.name: qbDwsIotIfLastRangeTime
qbDwsIotIfLastRangeTime.description: The value of MIB II's sysUpTime object at the last time when this IOT is ranged

qbDwsIotIfStatsTable.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsTable
qbDwsIotIfStatsTable.description: The Quantum Bridge IOT's terminal table. One entry per each RT.

qbDwsIotIfStatsEntry.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsEntry
qbDwsIotIfStatsEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum DWS Interface Statistics Table.

qbDwsIotIfStatsUtil.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsUtil
qbDwsIotIfStatsUtil.description: The object indicates the utilization of the Network Interface transmission rate capacity by the IOT DWS interface. This object is specified in percents.

qbDwsIotIfStatsOamRequests.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsOamRequests
qbDwsIotIfStatsOamRequests.description: The number of received downstream OAM request messages.

qbDwsIotIfStatsOamResponses.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsOamResponses
qbDwsIotIfStatsOamResponses.description: The number of transmitted upstream OAM response messages.

qbDwsIotIfStatsOamEvents.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsOamEvents
qbDwsIotIfStatsOamEvents.description: The number of OAM event messages originated by the interface.

qbDwsIotIfStatsOamBadMsgs.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsOamBadMsgs
qbDwsIotIfStatsOamBadMsgs.description: The number of wrong OAM messages received on this interface.

qbDwsIotIfStatsCrcErrs.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsCrcErrs
qbDwsIotIfStatsCrcErrs.description: The summary number of the IOT DWS CRC subframe and time slot header CRC errors.

qbDwsIotIfStatsTsHdrParityErrs.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsTsHdrParityErrs
qbDwsIotIfStatsTsHdrParityErrs.description: The number of Time Slot header parity errors that have been detected on the interface.

qbDwsIotIfStatsFrameLossErrs.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsFrameLossErrs
qbDwsIotIfStatsFrameLossErrs.description: The number of Loss frame errors that have been detected on the interface.

qbDwsIotIfStatsSignalLossErrs.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsSignalLossErrs
qbDwsIotIfStatsSignalLossErrs.description: The number of Loss signal errors that have been detected on the interface.

qbDwsIotIfStatsRxAal1Cells.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsRxAal1Cells
qbDwsIotIfStatsRxAal1Cells.description: The number of received AAL1 ATM cells.

qbDwsIotIfStatsTxAal1Cells.name: qbDwsIotIfStatsTxAal1Cells
qbDwsIotIfStatsTxAal1Cells.description: The number of transmitted ATM cells .

qbIotPktIfConfTable.name: qbIotPktIfConfTable
qbIotPktIfConfTable.description: The Quantum Bridge PKT configuration table contains cross-connections between Ethernet interfaces and corresponding PVC/AAL5 that are configured at a WAN port. An entry in the table may be created, destroyed or modified. This table lists all PVCs within the System that send/receive packet traffic to/from the ATM cloud.

qbIotPktIfConfEntry.name: qbIotPktIfConfEntry
qbIotPktIfConfEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum Bridge IP configuration table. For every IP traffic flow, there is a corresponding row in this table which contains a DWS interface index, and a VPI/VCI pair of PVC configured at a SONET port for a given DWS interface. The creation of a row in this table causes a corresponding entry in the atmVclTable of the ATM-MIB to be automatically created if an atmVclEntry with qbPktIotIfConfVpi and qbPktIotIfConfVci values does not exist. This corresponding entry can be removed only if the qbPktIotIfConfEntry is removed. The qbPktIotIfConfIndex of this table is an ifIndex of the DWS interface from the ifTable.

qbIotPktIfConfIndex.name: qbIotPktIfConfIndex
qbIotPktIfConfIndex.description: An interface index of the Ethernet port interface.

qbAtmIfIndex.name: qbAtmIfIndex
qbAtmIfIndex.description: An interface index of the ATM interface that is stacked on top of the WAN/SONET interface.

qbIotPktIfConfVpi.name: qbIotPktIfConfVpi
qbIotPktIfConfVpi.description: A VPI of the AAL5 PVC that connects this interface to the ATM cloud. This PVC is automatically configured at the SONET port of the WAN card (atmVclTable).

qbIotPktIfConfVci.name: qbIotPktIfConfVci
qbIotPktIfConfVci.description: A VCI of the AAL5 bi-directional PVC that connects this interface to the ATM cloud. This PVC is automatically configured or removed at the SONET port of the WAN card (atmVclTable).

qbIotPktIfConfConnName.name: qbIotPktIfConfConnName
qbIotPktIfConfConnName.description: The textual name of the connection(PVC) as specified by a user. It provides a non-volatile handle for this PVC. The supplied name in the qbPktIotIfConfPvcName is associated with the same PVC for as long as that PVC/conection remains.

qbIotPktIfConfRxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbIotPktIfConfRxTrafficDescrIndex
qbIotPktIfConfRxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this VCL.

qbIotPktIfConfTxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbIotPktIfConfTxTrafficDescrIndex
qbIotPktIfConfTxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this VCL.

qbIotPktIfConfAdminStatus.name: qbIotPktIfConfAdminStatus
qbIotPktIfConfAdminStatus.description: The desired administrative status of the packet connection The up and down states indicate that the traffic flow is enabled or disabled respectively across the ATM cloud.

qbIotPktIfConfOperStatus.name: qbIotPktIfConfOperStatus
qbIotPktIfConfOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the connect.

qbIotPktIfConfRowStatus.name: qbIotPktIfConfRowStatus
qbIotPktIfConfRowStatus.description: The status column for this IOT ENET interface. This OBJECT can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following values may be read: active(1) This object may only be set to createAndGo(4). Setting this object to active(1) when its value is already active(1) is a no-op. Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the agent to attempt to create and commit the row based on the contents of the objects in the row. If all necessary information is present in the row and the values are acceptable to the agent, the agent will change the status to active(1). If any of the necessary objects are not available, the agent will reject the creation request. Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove the corresponding entry in this table, and disable data traffic.

qbIotPktIfConfLoopback.name: qbIotPktIfConfLoopback
qbIotPktIfConfLoopback.description: This object enables loopback on the IOT ENET enedpoint.

qbIotAddrTable.name: qbIotAddrTable
qbIotAddrTable.description: The Quantum Bridge IOT address table. This table contains information to convert an IOT's address into an IOT's serial number. This table has two indexes: 1. Interface index of the IOAS interface to which a terminal connects. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same as the interface identified by the same value of ifIndex. 2. IOT terminal address. A row exists in this table for each discovered IOT terminal. Whenever an IOT is discovered a row is added to the table

qbIotAddrEntry.name: qbIotAddrEntry
qbIotAddrEntry.description: For every IOT terminal there is a row in this table. This contains the IOT address and serial number.

qbIotPortCrossConnTable.name: qbIotPortCrossConnTable
qbIotPortCrossConnTable.description: The Quantum Bridge IOT port cross-connection table. This table defines all IOT port point-to-point cross-connections within a single OAS system. The connection can be set between two Ethernet, two DS1 or two E1 ports on different IOTs. The table has two indexes: the interface index of the first end-point and the interface index of the second endpoint. Note: Connections that are listed in this table are not reflected in the atmVclTable.

qbIotPortCrossConnEntry.name: qbIotPortCrossConnEntry
qbIotPortCrossConnEntry.description: An entry in the Quantum Bridge qbIotPortConnTable two contains a connection between the same port type of different IOTs.

qbIotPortCrossConnEndpt1IfIndex.name: qbIotPortCrossConnEndpt1IfIndex
qbIotPortCrossConnEndpt1IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the first IOT port((end-point) for the configured IOT cross-connect.

qbIotPortCrossConnEndpt2IfIndex.name: qbIotPortCrossConnEndpt2IfIndex
qbIotPortCrossConnEndpt2IfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the second IOT port(end-point) for the configured IOT cross-connect.

qbIotPortCrossConnAdminStatus.name: qbIotPortCrossConnAdminStatus
qbIotPortCrossConnAdminStatus.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this VCL.

qbIotPortCrossConnOperStatus.name: qbIotPortCrossConnOperStatus
qbIotPortCrossConnOperStatus.description: The current operational status of the connection.

qbIotPortCrossConnLastChange.name: qbIotPortCrossConnLastChange
qbIotPortCrossConnLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time this connection entered its current operational state.

qbIotPortCrossConnRxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbIotPortCrossConnRxTrafficDescrIndex
qbIotPortCrossConnRxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the transmit direction of this connection.

qbIotPortCrossConnTxTrafficDescrIndex.name: qbIotPortCrossConnTxTrafficDescrIndex
qbIotPortCrossConnTxTrafficDescrIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ATM Traffic Descriptor Table which applies to the receive direction of this connection.

qbIotPortCrossConnName.name: qbIotPortCrossConnName
qbIotPortCrossConnName.description: The textual name of the connection as specified by a user. It provides a non-volatile handle for this connection. The supplied name in the qbIotPortConnName is associated with the same connection for as long as that conection remains.

qbIotPortCrossConnRowStatus.name: qbIotPortCrossConnRowStatus
qbIotPortCrossConnRowStatus.description: The status of the port connect entry. Changing the value of this object from 'active' to 'destroy' will remove this entry from the database. It will disrupt traffic between two IOT packet interfaces.

qbIotPortCrossConnLoopback.name: qbIotPortCrossConnLoopback
qbIotPortCrossConnLoopback.description: This object enables loopback on this IOT to IOT port enedpoint. The endpoint on which loopback is enabled is defined by qbIotPortCrossConnLoopbackEndpt.

qbIotPortCrossConnLoopbackEndpt.name: qbIotPortCrossConnLoopbackEndpt
qbIotPortCrossConnLoopbackEndpt.description: This object defines loopback on the selected endpoint.

qbTContNumber.name: qbTContNumber
qbTContNumber.description: The total number of provisioned Ethernet to ATM PVCs.

qbTContTable.name: qbTContTable
qbTContTable.description: The Quantum Bridge Traffic Container table(TCons) contains traffic containers of IOTs.

qbTContEntry.name: qbTContEntry
qbTContEntry.description: An entry in the qbTContTable. There is one entry in the table per IOT on the PON for Release 3.0. The creation of a row in the qbSysIotTable causes a corresponding entry in this table to be automatically created. The deletion of a row in the qbSysIotTable causes a corresponding entry in this table to be automatically removed.

qbTContIndex.name: qbTContIndex
qbTContIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the row of the Traffic Container Table. Note tht this value can be set to 1 only for Release 3.0.

qbTContType.name: qbTContType
qbTContType.description: The Traffic container type. Note that this object can be set to type1 for Release 3.0

qbTContMaxBw.name: qbTContMaxBw
qbTContMaxBw.description: The maximum bandwidth to be assigned to this TCONT. Note that the read-only access is supported for Release 3.0

qbTContFixedBw.name: qbTContFixedBw
qbTContFixedBw.description: The lower limit of bandwidth for this TCONT.

qbTContAssuredBw.name: qbTContAssuredBw
qbTContAssuredBw.description: The guaranteed minimum bandwidth for this TCONT. TCONT. Note that the read-only access is supported for Release 3.0

qbTContGrantNum.name: qbTContGrantNum
qbTContGrantNum.description: FSAN grant number that is assigned to this TCONT. Note that the read-only access is supported for Release 3.0

qbDwsIotRxLos.name: qbDwsIotRxLos
qbDwsIotRxLos.description: A qbDwsIotRxLos trap indicates Loss of Signal by the IOT's. This trap is generated by an IOT when Analog DS1/E1 Analog or Digital Los occur.

qbDwsRxIoasLos.name: qbDwsRxIoasLos
qbDwsRxIoasLos.description: A qbDwsRxIoasLos trap indicates Loss of Signal by the IOAS's DWS receiver. This trap is generated by an IOAS DWS card when no signal from an IOT is detected within the timeslot window.

qbDwsIoasTxFailure.name: qbDwsIoasTxFailure
qbDwsIoasTxFailure.description: A qbDwsTxFailure trap indicates that the IOAS card transmitter does not work. The trap is generated by an IOAS card when the IOAS DWS card transmitter problem is detected. The trap contains the DWS card interface index.

qbDwsIotRangeTimeout.name: qbDwsIotRangeTimeout
qbDwsIotRangeTimeout.description: A qbDwsTxFailure trap indicates that IOT not responding during the ranging process.

qbDwsCompliance.name: qbDwsCompliance
qbDwsCompliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

qbDwsNetGroupInfo.name: qbDwsNetGroupInfo
qbDwsNetGroupInfo.description: The set of all accessible objects in the DWS Network Group of this MIB.

qbDwsIotGroupInfo.name: qbDwsIotGroupInfo
qbDwsIotGroupInfo.description: The set of all accessible objects in the IOT Group of this MIB.

qbDwsPktGroupInfo.name: qbDwsPktGroupInfo
qbDwsPktGroupInfo.description: The set of all accessible objects in the Packet Group ofthis MIB.

qbDwsIotAddrGroupInfo.name: qbDwsIotAddrGroupInfo
qbDwsIotAddrGroupInfo.description: The set of all accessible objects in the IOT address group of this MIB.
